          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">VP impeachment and family tussle</h2> 
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/vp-impeachment-and-family-tussle.png" alt="The Philippine parliament voted to impeach VP Sara Duterte over corruption allegations" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
         <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            Sara Duterte and all former presidents have been removed from the National Security Council to ‘reorganize and streamline’ it. Credits: Rolex dela Peña/EPA
          </p>
        </mj-text>

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: The Philippine parliament voted to impeach VP Sara Duterte ahead of the May midterm elections over threats against President Ferdinand Marcos Jr.</strong></p> 

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The Philippine parliament <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-02-2025-h1-1-voted-to-impeach" target="_blank">voted to impeach</a> Vice-President Sara Duterte over allegations of corruption and threats against President Ferdinand Marcos Jr. 215 out of 306 lawmakers voted for impeachment. The case will be moved to the Senate for trial. If convicted, Duterte would be removed from office and barred from future public positions, ruining a chance for a potential 2028 presidential bid.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The impeachment comes ahead of the May midterm elections, seen as a test of Marcos' leadership. Duterte denies the charges and says they are a political vendetta. His brother condemned the move as persecution, while Marcos has remained silent despite previously dismissing it as unnecessary. The move <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-02-2025-h1-2-amplifies-the-fued" target="_blank">amplifies the feud</a> between the two powerful political families, the Dutertes and Marcos, who have held family dynasties in Philippine politics.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Sara Duterte and Ferdinand Marcos Jr.'s <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-02-2025-h1-3-alliance-was-very-close" target="_blank">alliance was very close</a> throughout their 2022 election campaign. However, due to political and diplomatic differences, it quickly unraveled. Their split deepened as Marcos <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-02-2025-h1-4-pivoted-the-philiphines" target="_blank">pivoted the Philippines</a> back to the US, reversing Duterte’s father's <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-02-2025-h1-5-pro-china-stance" target="_blank">pro-China stance</a> and softening stance on the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-02-2025-h1-6-icc-drug-war-probe" target="_blank">ICC drug war probe</a>.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
 
