        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Argentina pulls out of WHO</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/argentina-pulls-out-of-who.png" alt="Argentina decided to withdraw from WHO over the mismanagement of COVID-19 pandemic" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            Argentina President Javier Milei arrives to speak at Mar-a-Lago in Palm Beach. Credits: Alex Brandon/AP
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: Argentina decided to withdraw from the WHO over the mismanagement of the COVID-19 pandemic. This follows a pattern in which Latin American countries adopt Trump’s policies.</strong></p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Argentina has withdrawn from the World Health Organization (WHO). Argentina President Javier Milei's government <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-02-2025-h2-7-cited-the-same-disagreements" target="_blank">cited the same disagreements</a> as his ally President Trump's health management, particularly during the COVID-19 pandemic, accusing WHO of promoting prolonged lockdowns and undermining national sovereignty. Argentine officials claimed the withdrawal would provide "greater flexibility to implement policies" in Argentina's interests and "greater availability of resources."</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The move marks Argentina's latest step in reshaping its international commitments <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-02-2025-h2-8-under-milei-administration" target="_blank">under Milei's administration</a>, which is very different from the previous administration. The WHO did not experience as much shock as when the US withdrew, as Argentina's contribution to the WHO is much less than that of the US, which is by far the most significant competitor.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">This move also shows a pattern emerging in Latin America, where conservative regional leaders have adopted policies that mirror Trump's stance on border security, trade, and migration. Milei’s Ministry of National Security has also said it will reinforce its border with Bolivia by erecting a 200-meter fence in Argentina’s Salta province. <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-02-2025-h2-9-other-examples" target="_blank">Other examples</a> include Ecuador's tariff on Mexico and El Salvador’s offer to Marco Rubio.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
