        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Sheikh Hasina’s home destroyed</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: Sheikh Hasina’s house was burned down by protesters who viewed the house as a symbol of fascism.</strong></p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Thousands of protesters in Bangladesh have <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-02-2025-h3-10-torched-and-demolished" target="_blank">torched and demolished</a> the historic home of Sheikh Mujibur Rahman, the country's founding leader and father of ousted Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina. The attack prompted Hasina's online speech from exile in India, where she urged her supporters to resist the interim government led by Muhammad Yunus. 
      </p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Student-led protesters viewed the house as a "symbol of fascism" and targeted other properties linked to Hasina's Awami League. The unrest stems from a student uprising that toppled Hasina's 15-year rule, accusing her of corruption and suppression. Attackers also targeted several houses and businesses belonging to Hasina’s Awami League supporters. The rally was organized alongside a broader call, dubbed “Bulldozer Procession,” to disrupt Hasina’s address.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         The interim government seeks Hasina's extradition from India, which <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-02-2025-h3-11-india-has-not-complied" target="_blank">India has not complied</a> with and likely won’t. She has called for a UN investigation into alleged killings during the uprising and accused the acting government of <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-02-2025-h3-12-perpetrating-genocide" target="_blank">perpetrating genocide</a> and not protecting Bangladesh's minorities who have been attacked in these protests.
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>

