      <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
          <strong>🇬🇧 UK PM Starmer under fire for Chagos deal</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Sir Keir Starmer endured some tough questioning at PMQs about the UK’s agreement to transfer sovereignty of the Chagos Islands to Mauritius. The UK and Mauritius <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-02-2025-br2-16-denied-reports" target="_blank">denied reports</a> that the deal’s cost had doubled to over $ 22 billion, but Tory leader Kemi Badenoch and Reform UK’s Nigel Farage said this was to attack the agreement.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The agreement, which includes leasing Diego Garcia for 99 years, is now on hold pending a review by Donald Trump. The UK argues that legal uncertainty could jeopardize the base, while critics claim that no binding ruling required the handover. Mauritius, a former British colony, has long argued that it was <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-02-2025-br2-17-illegally-forced-to-give" target="_blank">illegally forced to give</a> the Chagos Islands away in return for its independence in 1968.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

